00:56:36.109 --> 00:56:40.280 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
You’ll probably want to listen
to that song again and again.

00:56:40.280 --> 00:56:43.850 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Or you might even want to sing it yourself.

00:56:43.850 --> 00:56:48.521 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Our hope is one of the things
we want to focus on.

00:56:48.521 --> 00:56:51.491 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And this will have an effect on us;

00:56:51.491 --> 00:56:54.494 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
it will contribute to our being joyful.

00:56:55.662 --> 00:56:58.832 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Let’s conclude
this month’s program with a visit

00:56:58.832 --> 00:57:01.101 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
to a truly beautiful part of the earth:

00:57:01.101 --> 00:57:03.136 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Martinique.

00:57:03.136 --> 00:57:05.638 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
This island in the eastern Caribbean

00:57:05.638 --> 00:57:09.676 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
measures just 50 miles
(or about 80 kilometers)

00:57:09.676 --> 00:57:13.046 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
by 22 miles (or 35 kilometers).

00:57:13.046 --> 00:57:16.816 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Yet, Martinique,
nicknamed the Island of Flowers,

00:57:16.816 --> 00:57:20.854 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
has stunning geographic diversity,
with beaches,

00:57:20.854 --> 00:57:23.990 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
forests, rivers,

00:57:23.990 --> 00:57:28.161 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
sugarcane plantations,
and rugged mountains.

00:57:28.161 --> 00:57:30.497 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
The highest point is Mount Pelée,

00:57:30.497 --> 00:57:33.633 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
infamous for causing
the deadliest volcanic eruption

00:57:33.633 --> 00:57:36.035 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
in the 20th century.

00:57:36.035 --> 00:57:39.172 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
When Pelée erupted in 1902,

00:57:39.172 --> 00:57:44.043 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
nearly 30,000 people died
because they ignored the warnings.

00:57:44.043 --> 00:57:47.981 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
This tragedy is often discussed
by our brothers in the ministry.

00:57:47.981 --> 00:57:50.884 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Today, more than 4,700 publishers

00:57:50.884 --> 00:57:53.386 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
in 62 congregations

00:57:53.386 --> 00:57:55.855 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
share the good news in eight languages,

00:57:55.855 --> 00:57:59.225 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
including French, English,
French Sign Language,

00:57:59.225 --> 00:58:03.029 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Arabic, and Creole of Martinique.

00:58:03.029 --> 00:58:06.533 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
They conduct more than 4,500 Bible studies

00:58:06.533 --> 00:58:08.968 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
—nearly one per publisher.

00:58:08.968 --> 00:58:13.206 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Over one million tourists
visit this beautiful island every year

00:58:13.206 --> 00:58:15.208 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
—many by cruise ship.

00:58:15.208 --> 00:58:17.944 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
This presents a unique preaching opportunity.

00:58:18.711 --> 00:58:23.416 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
The city of Le Marin
hosts 55,000 boaters annually.

00:58:23.416 --> 00:58:25.618 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Here our brothers preach

00:58:25.618 --> 00:58:28.154 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“sailboat to sailboat.”

00:58:28.154 --> 00:58:30.957 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
This is the city of La Trinité.

00:58:30.957 --> 00:58:33.226 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
A Creole of Martinique congregation

00:58:33.226 --> 00:58:35.461 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
was formed here two years ago.

00:58:35.461 --> 00:58:39.766 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Today, the congregation has 91 publishers

00:58:39.766 --> 00:58:41.768 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and 10 regular pioneers.

00:58:41.768 --> 00:58:45.371 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
They preach
in the countryside, the foothills,

00:58:45.371 --> 00:58:48.408 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
wherever people can be found.

00:58:48.408 --> 00:58:51.844 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Our brothers and sisters
in La Trinité, Martinique,

00:58:51.844 --> 00:58:55.682 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
send you
their warm Christian love and greetings.

00:58:55.682 --> 00:58:58.785 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
From the World Headquarters
of Jehovah’s Witnesses,

00:58:58.785 --> 00:59:01.788 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
this is JW Broadcasting!

